    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix pattern2 TDD configuration handling in gNB\n\n### Summary\nThe NR gNB configuration handling for TDD pattern2 had several issues that caused improper memory allocation and configuration parsing. The main problem was that pattern2 memory was always allocated even when not configured, and there was no proper function to check if pattern2 was actually configured by the user.\n\nThis caused issues when running gNB with TDD configurations where pattern2 was not explicitly defined in the configuration file, leading to crashes during RRC configuration processing.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/GNB_APP/gnb_config.c`: \n  * Added `is_pattern2_config()` function to properly check if pattern2 parameters are configured\n  * Modified `prepare_scc()` to initialize pattern2 as NULL instead of always allocating memory\n  * Updated `fill_scc_sim()` to safely handle NULL pattern2\n  * Fixed `fix_scc()` to properly check pattern2 configuration before accessing it\n  * Added proper pattern2 configuration handling in `get_scc_config()` that reads parameters into temporary variables first, checks if configured, and only then allocates pattern2 memory\n- Added required header includes for logging and assertions\n\n"
}